  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1010', 'Periwinkle Sky', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Light purple with small gold and large white crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base darkens; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base darkens; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1011', 'Frosted Berries', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte white with large purple and small blue crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy but color remains; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and fades to white; pink crystals fade but blue crystals remain and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1012', 'Haystack', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte pale yellow with tan and orange crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy but color remains; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and color fades; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1013', 'Papaya', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte orange with black, orange and tan crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy but color remains; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and color fades; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1014', 'Pink Plum', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte pink with purple and white crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy and lightens; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and white; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1015', 'Cloverfield', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte bright/lime green with blue, green and yellow crystals of varying sizes Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy and darkens; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and darkens; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Jungle Gems', 'CG1016', 'Asteroid', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Matte grey with black and white crystals Cone 6 oxidation: Base becomes glossy but color remains; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Cone 10 reduction: Base becomes glossy and color turns blueish grey; crystals fade and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG001', 'White Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : White Engobe fires matte white . Engobes are used to coat your clay body to your preferred finish/color and are a great base to achieve variability in your glaze results. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : Has a slight sheen. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG002', 'Speckled Buff Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Buff Engobe fires matte ivory with brown speckles. Engobes are used to coat your clay body to your preferred finish/color and are a great base to achieve v in your glaze results. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : No change. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG003', 'Brick Red Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Brick Red Engobe fires matte red/brown. Engobes are used to coat your clay body to your preferred finish/color and are a great base to achieve v in your glaze results. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : No change. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG004', 'Dark Brown Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Dark Brown Engobe fires matte brown. Engobes are used to coat your clay body to your preferred finish/color and are a great base to achieve in your glaze results. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : No change. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG005', 'Black Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Black Engobe fires matte black. Engobes are used to coat your clay body to your preferred finish/color and are a great base to achieve in your glaze results. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : No change. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG006', 'Sparkle Black Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Sparkle Black Engobe fires matte black with metallic specks. Specks may produce texture. Highly stable. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : No change to base color. Specks bloom and become matte. Remains stable. Tips: To enhance the sparkle and improve texture, use your fingers to burnish/polish the surface of the ware before the last layer is dry. Polishing is not needed when used in combination. Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze (SW004) Zinc-Free Clear to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. SW004 Zinc-Free Clear is recommended for a black finish. SW001 Stoneware Clear will change the color to a rich brown and affect the sparkle. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Stoneware Engobes', 'EG007', 'Terracotta Engobe', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 6 oxidation (larger image) : Terracotta Engobe fires matte. Highly stable. Cone 10 reduction (smaller image) : Color darkens. Remains stable. Tips: Can be applied to wet clay, greenware or soft fired, cone 04 bisque. Engobes are often used for a variety of decorative techniques, such as sgraffito and majolica. Fires matte. Apply clear glaze to intensify color or for use on dinnerware. Engobes will impact glaze results when used as a base. Engobes are used to change the color of your clay color surface without cross contamination and easy clean up in your studio. Can be used in oxidation or reduction firings. Results may vary. The choice of clay body, thickness of application, firing process, and temperature will greatly affect the fired results. Always test your application on your clay body in your kiln environment.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-103', 'Sea Spray', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Sea Spray is a glossy, pale blueish gray glaze that breaks a darker, blueish gray with yellowing. Semi-Transparent at three coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to an opaque cream that breaks over texture and pools mint green. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-106', 'Tidal Pool', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Tidal Pool is a glossy, bluish olive glaze that breaks a darker, blueish olive. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a mottled green/white/brown that breaks over texture and pools solid green. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-107', 'Amber Ash', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Amber Ash is a glossy, honey colored glaze with black specks. It has an orangish brown stain. Transparent at three coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens to a variegated gold/brown/blue that breaks over texture and pools blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-113', 'Spanish Moss', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Spanish Moss is a matte, olive green glaze that breaks a dark blueish green. It has an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to an olive brown/green that breaks over texture and has a gloss finish. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-117', 'Waterfall', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Waterfall is a glossy, dark blue glaze with an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to an olive green/brown that breaks over texture. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-119', 'Burnished Steel', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Burnished Steel is a matte, metallic dark gray glaze. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a metallic black that breaks over texture and pools a flat metallic gray. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-120', 'Black Ice', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Black Ice is a glossy, metallic black glaze. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color remains and develops an iridescent finish. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-121', 'Copper Adventurine', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Copper Adventurine is a glossy, metallic dark brown and copper glaze with a yellow stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens to a sparkly black that breaks over texture and pools brown/red. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-122', 'Malachite', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Malachite is a mottled dark green and metallic black glaze with a matte finish. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a glossy green that breaks over texture and pools a metallic gray; green/gray crystallization can occur. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-123', 'Patina', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Patina is a matte, mottled mint green and copper glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a glossy pink that breaks over texture; mint green crystallization can occur. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-124', 'Stormy Blue', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Stormy Blue is a matte, metallic silver and blue glaze with a mottled appearance. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a glossy yellow that breaks over texture; blue crystallization can occur. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-125', 'Sahara Sands', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Sahara Sands is a glossy, variegated tan glaze with an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent gold/brown that breaks over texture and pools with some lighter variation. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Stable glaze. Will not move or craze with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-132', 'Rust Red', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Rust Red is a glossy, brownish red glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a dark brown/red that breaks over texture. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Stable glaze. Will not move or craze with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-134', 'Mirror Blue', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Mirror Blue is a glossy, vibrant blue glaze. Semi-Transparent at three coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-135', 'Rare Earth', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Rare Earth is a glossy, brown glaze that breaks dark brown with a brown stain. Transparent at three coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens to an opaque brown/gold that breaks over texture and pools gold. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-136', 'Lapis Lagoon', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Lapis Lagoon is a glossy, teal glaze. Transparent at three coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a transparent green that breaks and pools over texture. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-137', 'Black Adventurine', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Black Adventurine is a matte, mottled black and metallic dark copper glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a glossy, metallic black/gray that breaks over texture. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-140', 'Toasted Almond', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Toasted Almond is a matte, mottled tan and light brown glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to white and breaks over texture; yellow crystallization can occur. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-142', 'Grass', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Grass is a glossy, green glaze with an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent, variegated olive green/blue that breaks over texture and pools blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Stable glaze. Will not move or craze with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-143', 'Cactus Flower', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Cactus Flower is a glossy, orangish pink glaze with an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent, variegated brown/orange/blue that breaks over texture and pools blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Stable glaze. Will not move or craze with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-144', 'Dark Amethyst', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Dark Amethyst is a glossy, mottled glaze with dark purple and taupe. It has a dark brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent, variegated brown/green/blue that breaks over texture and pools blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze will move slightly with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-145', 'Ginger Root', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Ginger Root is a glossy, mottled taupe and orangish brown glaze with an orangish brown stain. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent gold/brown that breaks over texture and pools blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze will move slightly with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-146', 'Rain Cloud', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Rain Cloud is a glossy, mottled light and dark gray glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to a semi-translucent light brown/gray that breaks over texture and pools with some lighter variation. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Stable glaze. Will not move or craze with three coats. Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-152', 'Denim Blue', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Denim blue is a glossy, blueish gray glaze with the look of denim that has fine dark blue specks. Semi-Transparent at 2 – 3 coats. . Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): No color change. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: Overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-153', 'Caribbean Blue', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Caribbean Blue is a glossy, ocean blue glaze that breaks a darker blue. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color turns teal. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. Tip: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-155', 'Holiday Green', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Holiday Green is a glossy, deep yellow-green glaze that breaks a darker green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'El-155', 'Holiday Green', 'Cone 06', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Holiday Green is a glossy, deep yellow-green glaze that breaks a darker green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-156', 'Bluegrass', 'Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Bluegrass is a glossy, deep blue-green glaze that breaks a darker, green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color turns green. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'El-156', 'Bluegrass', 'Cone 06', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Bluegrass is a glossy, deep blue-green glaze that breaks a darker, green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color turns green. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-158', 'Pine Needles', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Pine Needles is a glossy, rust brown, that breaks a yellow-green. Semi-Transparent at 2 – 3 coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color changes to brown. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-159', 'Emerald Green', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Emerald Green is a glossy, dark blue green glaze, that breaks a darker green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens to green. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-160', 'Foliage Green', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Foliage Green is a glossy yellow green glaze, that breaks a darker yellow-green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-161', 'Bottle Green', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Bottle Green is an iridescent dark green glaze that breaks a darker green. Semi-Transparent at 3 coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color turns olive. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-207', 'Gold Mine', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Gold Mine is a glossy, olive taupe glaze. It has medium light blue and small tan crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Base glaze changes to a mottled orange/white/green and breaks over texture; crystals remain and melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-208', 'Moss Creek', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Moss Creek is a matte, olive green glaze that breaks a dark blueish green. It has an orangish brown stain. It has large light and dark blue crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Base glaze changes to a variegated olive/red and breaks over texture; crystals fade. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-209', 'Night Sky', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Night Sky is a glossy, denim blue glaze with a dark gray stain. It has large and medium light blue crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Base glaze changes to brown/green and breaks over texture; crystals melt. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-211', 'Volcanic Glow', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Volcanic Glow is a glossy, dark grayish taupe glaze with a brown stain. It has large red crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Base glaze changes to brown/gold and breaks over texture; crystals melt and are red/blue. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'EL-212', 'Spotted Walnut', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Spotted Walnut is a matte, mottled tan and light brown glaze. It has medium black and white crystals with black specks. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Base glaze changes to white with some crystallization; crystals melt into base glaze. Enhanced mobility. Surface issues may occur. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'E-Z Stroke Translucent Underglazes', 'EZ002', 'Cinderella Pink', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Cinderella Pink is a translucent underglaze suitable for use with a number of decorating techniques including airbrushing, antiquing and brushstrokes. Cone 6 oxidation: Color mostly fades. Recommended clear: SW001 Stoneware Clear. Cone 10 reduction: Color completely fades. Recommended clear: SW001 Stoneware Clear.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'E-Z Stroke Translucent Underglazes', 'EZ003', 'Irish Green', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation: Irish Green is a translucent underglaze suitable for use with a number of decorating techniques including airbrushing, antiquing and brushstrokes. Cone 6 oxidation: Dull, yellower lime green. Recommended clear: SW001 Stoneware Clear. Cone 10 reduction: Dull, yellower lime green. Recommended clear: SW001 Stoneware Clear.'),
