  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Elements and Elements Chunkies', 'FN-218', 'Green Sapphire', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Green Sapphire is an iridescent dark bluish green glaze. It is transparent at three coats. Not dinnerware safe. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): Color darkens and breaks brown; an iridescent sheen develops. Enhanced mobility. Not dinnerware safe. TIP: This glaze WILL move. Take care when using on vertical pieces reduce glaze thickness towards the bottom third to minimize run-off. This glaze will pinhole at three coats. Not overglaze compatible.'),
