  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Snow Gems', 'SG303', 'Citrus Snow Gem', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Creates a white, textured surface with chartreuse and orange crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): No change. Cone 10 reduction (small photo): No change.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Snow Gems', 'SG304', 'Berry Snow Gem', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Creates a white, textured surface with purple and red crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): No change. Cone 10 reduction (small photo): Purple crystals fade.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Snow Gems', 'SG305', 'Spearmint Snow Gem', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (large photo): Creates a white, textured surface with green and blue crystals. Cone 6 oxidation (small photo): No change. Cone 10 reduction (small photo): Color of crystals slightly fade.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-201', 'Speckled Pink-A-Boo', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image): Speckled Pink-A-Boo is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with maroon specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image): Semi-Transparent. Color slightly lightens. Specks bleed.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-206', 'Speckled Sunkissed', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Sunkissed is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with maroon specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. No color change, specks blur'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-209', 'Speckled Jaded', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Jaded is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with yellow, orange and blue specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. Color lightens to medium brown. Specks remain.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-210', 'Speckled Teal Next Time', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Teal Next Time is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with white specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. No color change.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-211', 'Speckled Blue Yonder', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Blue Yonder is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with white specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Semi-Transparent. Color slightly lightens. Specks remain same.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-212', 'Speckled Moody Blue', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Moody Blue is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with white specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. Color lightens to medium brown. Specks remain.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-213', 'Speckled Grapel', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Grapel is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with blue specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Transparent. Color Slightly lightens. Specks bleed.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-215', 'Speckled Tuxedo', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Tuxedo is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with white specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. Color slightly Darkens.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-216', 'Speckled Cotton Tail', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Cotton Tail is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with yellow, orange and blue specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. Specks blur and slightly bleed.'),
  ('commercial', 'Mayco', 'Speckled Stroke & Coat', 'SP-226', 'Speckled Green Thumb', 'Cone 06 / Cone 10 / Cone 6', 'Cone 06 oxidation (larger image) : Speckled Green Thumb is a heavily pigmented, viscous Stroke & Coat glaze with black specks that can be used for brush strokes or opaque coverage. One coat will create a translucent finish with subsequent coats adding opacity. We suggest two to three coats for full opacity and all over coverage. Will fire to a gloss finish without clear glaze. Cone 6 oxidation (smaller image) : Opaque. No color change.'),
